Exercise 02 — Shellcode Injection
===================================

There is no win() function this time.
You must inject your own machine code into the buffer
and redirect execution to it.

The stack is executable (-z execstack).

  Compile:
    gcc -fno-stack-protector -z execstack -no-pie -o target target.c

  Find the buffer address:
    gdb ./target → break vulnerable → run → p &buffer

  Build your payload:
    [NOP sled \x90 ...] + [shellcode] + [padding] + [buffer address]

  Your shellcode must call write(1, "[SUCCESS]\n", 10).

When you see [SUCCESS], run `horizon done`.
